  "triage_outcome": "escalated",
  "triage_reasoning": "The finding appears to be a false positive / already mitigated, requiring human security engineer verification. Two key issues: (1) DISCREPANCY: The actual CVE-2023-42502 describes HTTP Host header spoofing for dataset links (fixed in Superset 3.0.0), but the scanner describes an open redirect via the post-login 'next' parameter \u2014 these are different vulnerabilities. (2) ALREADY MITIGATED: Flask-AppBuilder 5.2.1 (pinned in this fork's requirements/base.txt) already calls get_safe_redirect() in all auth view login handlers (AuthDBView, AuthLDAPView, AuthOAuthView, AuthSAMLView). This function validates the 'next' parameter by checking the URL host against the request host or the configurable FAB_SAFE_REDIRECT_HOSTS list, blocking external redirects. Additionally, Superset's own redirect_to_login() in superset/views/utils.py only constructs the 'next' value from server-side request.path/request.full_path (relative paths, not user-supplied URLs). The initialization/__init__.py locale redirect also uses get_safe_redirect(). Since no unprotected redirect path exists in the current codebase, auto-remediation would mean applying redundant protections. A security engineer should verify this assessment and confirm closure.",
  "fix_session_id": null,
  "pr_url": null,
  "status": "escalated"
}
